The paper deals with recommendation systems, which are typically studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The use of graphs and collaborative ranking algorithms also suggests the Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on improving the reliability of recommendation lists suggests the Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC) sub-category.
